South Africa has recorded 1 913 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 685 155. The country has also recorded 145 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 17 248. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 145 more COVID-19 related deaths: “42 from KwaZulu-Natal, 41 from Gauteng, 1 from Eastern Cape, 11 from Free State, 24 from Limpopo, 11 from Mpumalanga, 7 from the Northern Cape and 8 from Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 318 514. The number of recoveries now stands at 618 127, this translates to a recovery rate of 90%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 685 155 the total number of deaths is 17 248 and the total number of recoveries is 618 127. pic.twitter.com/OO3zAfivht — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) October 7, 2020 